    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips, then add to a baking tray (or two!) with your <strong>five-spice mix</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, 1/2 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690189150811-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690189150811-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690189150811-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690189150811-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690189150811-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chips are cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very large drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Add the <strong>diced</strong> <strong>chicken breast</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>cornflour</strong> and give it a good mix up until all the chicken is coated</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690189154078-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690189154078-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690189154078-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690189154078-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690189154078-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pan is very hot, add the <strong>coated chicken</strong> and cook for 5-6 min on each side until golden and crispy and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>crispy chicken</strong></p><p>Once crispy, transfer to a plate and set aside and reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690189156758-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690189156758-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690189156758-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690189156758-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690189156758-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> in half (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into small cubes</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Finely slice your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> into rounds</p><p>Trim, then finely slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1690189159758-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1690189159758-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1690189159758-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1690189159758-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1690189159758-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with any remaining oil</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>pepper</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong> and <strong>half </strong>of the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(save the rest for later!) and cook for 3-4 min or until fragrant</p><p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>soy sauce</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>honey</strong>, <strong>chilli relish</strong> and <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> – this is your <strong>sticky chilli sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1690189162930-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1690189162930-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1690189162930-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1690189162930-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1690189162930-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> sticky chilli sauce </strong>to the pan and cook for 3 min or until the sauce begins to thicken and the pepper has softened</p><p>While the sauce thickens, chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Once thickened, add the<strong> crispy chicken </strong>to the pan and cook for 1 min further until the chicken is coated in the sauce – this is your <strong>sticky chilli chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1690189165841-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1690189165841-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1690189165841-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1690189165841-x1000.jpg",
